name: Mons Vinogradov
origin: Aleksandr Pavlovich; Soviet geochemist and cosmochemist (1895-1975).

name: Montes Haemus
origin: Named for range in the Balkans.

name: Montes Harbinger
origin: Harbingers of dawn on crater Aristarchus.

name: Mont Blanc
origin: Named for terrestrial mountain in Alps.

name: Mons Piton
origin: Named from Mt. Piton on Tenerife Islands.

name: Montes Spitzbergen
origin: German for "sharp peaks", and named for resemblance to the terrestrial island group.

name: Mons Argaeus
origin: Named from peak in Asia Minor (now Erciyas Dagi).

name: Montes Riphaeus
origin: Named from range in Asia (now Ural Mountains).

name: Mons Tai
origin: Named from terrestrial Mount Tai, in Shandong, China.
